<H2>Logging the QSO</H2>
<DIV ID="Frame12" DIR="LTR" STYLE="float: left; width: 16.5cm; height: 1.97cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; background: #ffffff">
	<P STYLE="margin-top: 0.21cm"><IMG SRC="UserGuide_html_m112f565d.png" NAME="graphics14" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=624 BORDER=0><BR CLEAR=LEFT><I>Illustration
	14: Commands in &quot;Active&quot; state</I>
</DIV>
In the &ldquo;Active&rdquo; state
the commands available are:
&ldquo;Start QSO&rdquo; - moves
ZZALOG to &ldquo;Enter QSO&rdquo; state with any details already
typed in are kept.
&ldquo;Add QSO&rdquo; - will
start logging a QSO that has already occurred.
&ldquo;Edit QSO&rdquo; - will
enable editing a QSO that has already been logged.
&ldquo;Delete QSO&rdquo; - will
remove the QSO from the log.
&ldquo;View QSO&rdquo; - will
open the selected QSO for viewing &ndash; and checking DXCC status
etc.
Clicking &ldquo;Start QSO&rdquo;
will cause the QSO date and time and the information obtained from
the rig to become fixed. It also makes a new set of commands
available:
<DIV ID="Frame13" DIR="LTR" STYLE="float: left; width: 16.5cm; height: 1.98cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; background: #ffffff">
	<P STYLE="margin-top: 0.21cm"><IMG SRC="UserGuide_html_m49d19ab4.png" NAME="graphics15" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=624 BORDER=0><BR CLEAR=LEFT><I>Illustration
	15: Commands in &quot;Enter QSO&quot; state</I>
</DIV>
&ldquo;Save&rdquo; - completes
the logging, by setting TIME_OFF field and reverts to &ldquo;Active&rdquo;
state.
&ldquo;Save &amp; View&rdquo; -
saves the logging, and keeps the QSO open for viewing.
&ldquo;Save &amp; New&rdquo; -
saves the logging, and starts a new QSO.
&ldquo;Save &amp; Edit&rdquo; -
saves the logging, but keeps the QSO in edit mode for further
updates.
&ldquo;Quit QSO&rdquo; - cancels
the logging and removes the QSO from the log.

